The MEC for Health in KwaZulu-Natal (KZN), Ms Nomagugu Simelane-Zulu has announced that the hospital visiting hours in KZN will be amended until further notice and is effective from Monday, 23 March. This after the announcement of a National State of Disaster by President Cyril Ramaphosa as South Africa deals with the global coronavirus pandemic. ” With the immune system of some in-hospital patients already compromised due to their ailments, the Department has a responsibility to maintain Infection Prevention and Control standards and minimize their exposure to people who could be carrying the virus unknowingly. ” said Simelane-Zulu. The revised visiting hours and visitors are as follows: Simelane-Zulu urged members of the public to co-operate.